The paper deals with the problem of reducing the depth of pre-trained deep neural networks while retaining their functionality on a given task. The specific use case discussed in the paper is face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed algorithm is based on supervised principal component analysis, which is a common technique used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in numerical experiments, which falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the algorithm to generate specialized networks for specific tasks, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
